In an effort to slow the spread of coronavirus, cities and states are implementing new restrictions, seemingly every hour.
The most effective tool is for everyone to stay home, but that’s a tough ask, especially when you’re living with young kids.
Kids especially need fresh air and movement, and you don’t have to be restricted to your backyard.
Possibly, and it might be necessary for child care since some parents will have to leave the house to work.
